      "role": "user",
      "content": "\"virtually no emissions\" seems a bit of a stretch doesn't it? i've read a lot about the carbon footprint of mining the materials for turbine blades and the waste issues with old blades. wouldn't it be more accurate to say they both have different types of environmental costs rather than just saying wind is cleaner?",
